    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What if I can't afford a bail bond at all?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "If you cannot afford a bail bond, there are several options to explore. Your public defender can request a bail reduction hearing before the judge. For minor, non-violent charges, you may be eligible for release on your own recognizance (OR release), which requires no payment. Additionally, Angel Bail Bonds works with families on flexible payment arrangements to make bail as affordable as possible. Call us at (405) 614-3000 to discuss your situation."
      }
